{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1781762922387,"sessionID":"ses_126b15e64ffeXip2YXWt9pDpCA","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_p9wwZ4C8mVmG5bPwhHx7Vmsw","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/005-verification-and-remediation/006-deep-review-017-021-remediation/checklist.md","offset":1,"limit":220},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/005-verification-and-remediation/006-deep-review-017-021-remediation/checklist.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: \"Verification Checklist: Deep-Review 017-021 Remediation [027/002/005/006]\"\n3: description: \"Quality gates for the 017-021 remediation. Items are pending at authoring time; each names the evidence the later implementation step must capture. The P1 and the per-finding coverage are the load-bearing gates.\"\n4: trigger_phrases:\n5:   - \"017-021 remediation checklist\"\n6:   - \"deep review remediation checklist\"\n7: importance_tier: \"important\"\n8: contextType: \"general\"\n9: _memory:\n10:   continuity:\n11:     packet_pointer: \"system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/005-verification-and-remediation/006-deep-review-017-021-remediation\"\n12:     last_updated_at: \"2026-06-17T00:00:00Z\"\n13:     last_updated_by: \"deep-review-remediation-author\"\n14:     recent_action: \"Authored verification gates incl. fix-completeness for 017-021 remediation\"\n15:     next_safe_action: \"verify c006 renderer then begin per-file remediation\"\n16:     blockers: []\n17:     completion_pct: 0\n18: ---\n19: # Verification Checklist: Deep-Review 017-021 Remediation\n20: \n21: <!-- SPECKIT_LEVEL: 3 -->\n22: <!-- SPECKIT_TEMPLATE_SOURCE: checklist + level3-arch | v2.2 -->\n23: \n24: ---\n25: \n26: <!-- ANCHOR:protocol -->\n27: ## Verification Protocol\n28: \n29: | Priority | Handling | Completion Impact |\n30: |----------|----------|-------------------|\n31: | **[P0]** | HARD BLOCKER | Cannot claim done until complete |\n32: | **[P1]** | Required | Must complete OR get user approval |\n33: | **[P2]** | Optional | Can defer with documented reason |\n34: \n35: Items below are PENDING — this is the authoring step; no fixes applied. Each item names the evidence the later implementation step must capture before marking `[x]`.\n36: <!-- /ANCHOR:protocol -->\n37: ---\n38: \n39: <!-- ANCHOR:pre-impl -->\n40: ## Pre-Implementation\n41: \n42: - [ ] CHK-001 [P0] All confirmed findings extracted into tasks.md\n43:   - **Evidence (target)**: every CONFIRMED row across the five syntheses maps to exactly one task; no orphan, no fabrication\n44: - [ ] CHK-002 [P0] Rejected/refuted/already-resolved findings excluded\n45:   - **Evidence (target)**: §3 Out of Scope + tasks.md T034 enumerate the excluded items (018 mimo-1; 019/020 D6/D7/D8; 021 B8/A3)\n46: - [ ] CHK-003 [P1] Each task names a target file + concrete change + synthesis trace + confidence tag\n47:   - **Evidence (target)**: tasks.md notation block + per-task `<trace:…>` and `{confirmed-by-code|needs-in-task-verification}`\n48: <!-- /ANCHOR:pre-impl -->\n49: ---\n50: \n51: <!-- ANCHOR:code-quality -->\n52: ## Code Quality\n53: \n54: - [ ] CHK-010 [P0] Each code fix is scoped to its synthesis-described change (no scope creep)\n55:   - **Evidence (target)**: diff per fix matches the cited remediation; reviewed deliverables stay behaviorally intact (NFR-C01)\n56: - [ ] CHK-011 [P1] c006 §0 hardening (if raw) handles glob/cmd-sub/metachar, not just word-splitting\n57:   - **Evidence (target)**: `set -f`/restructure applied; the shipped `\"$*\"` + `\"`-escape is superseded, not duplicated\n58: - [ ] CHK-012 [P1] `cancelledJobIds` cleared on EVERY terminal `setJobState` incl. `'failed'` (T012)\n59:   - **Evidence (target)**: job-store.ts delete on terminal transition; the `:69-75` \"cannot grow without bound\" comment is now literally true\n60: - [ ] CHK-013 [P1] Cited line numbers re-confirmed against live files before edit (esp. 021 :785-790/:802)\n61:   - **Evidence (target)**: each code task re-reads its cite (finding-is-a-hypothesis discipline)\n62: <!-- /ANCHOR:code-quality -->\n63: ---\n64: \n65: <!-- ANCHOR:testing -->\n66: ## Testing\n67: \n68: - [ ] CHK-020 [P0] Baseline captured before changes; whole gate re-run after; delta reported\n69:   - **Evidence (target)**: `baseline N failing {…} → now M: {…}` per touched suite (T032)\n70: - [ ] CHK-021 [P1] New unit coverage for `processBatches` shouldAbort + `isCancelRequestedFast` Set lifecycle (T014-T015)\n71:   - **Evidence (target)**: batch-processor.vitest.ts + job-store.vitest.ts assert the new behavior\n72: - [ ] CHK-022 [P1] c006 metacharacter verification cases pass (if raw renderer)\n73:   - **Evidence (target)**: queries with `*`, `$(…)`, backticks, `;`, `\\|`, `&`, `>` resolve to the verbatim typed string; arg-echo matches\n74: - [ ] CHK-023 [P2] 019/020 test fixtures use the real `labels[]` shape; tests still pass (T022)\n75:   - **Evidence (target)**: launcher-maintenance-guard + daemon-reelection-adoption-live fixtures updated; suites green\n76: <!-- /ANCHOR:testing -->\n77: ---\n78: \n79: <!-- ANCHOR:fix-completeness -->\n80: ## Fix Completeness\n81: \n82: - [ ] CHK-030 [P1] The single confirmed P1 (c006) is closed at its verified severity\n83:   - **Evidence (target)**: T001 establishes raw-vs-quoted; T002 quote-hardens (raw) or records a downgraded P2 doc-note (quoted), with renderer evidence cited\n84: - [ ] CHK-031 [P1] 017 systemic doc drift reconciled across all 7 children (T003)\n85:   - **Evidence (target)**: each child's spec/plan/tasks reflect shipped scope (or marked superseded); graph-metadata Status/Key Files match impl-summary\n86: - [ ] CHK-032 [P1] 019 doc cluster reconciled (paths, schema, TTL, limitation, module, fixtures) (T017-T022)\n87:   - **Evidence (target)**: `.opencode/bin/...` paths; `labels[]` schema; 180s TTL; per-tick embedding-queue protection; extracted module tracked\n88: - [ ] CHK-033 [P2] 018/021 cancellation + instrumentation P2s closed or accepted-with-reason\n89:   - **Evidence (target)**: T013/T027/T029/T030 done or each deferral documented against its synthesis\n90: - [ ] CHK-034 [P2] 017 c004 maintainability cluster + minor nits resolved or accepted-with-reason (T004-T011, T024-T026)\n91:   - **Evidence (target)**: each item fixed or carries a documented acceptance rationale\n92: <!-- /ANCHOR:fix-completeness -->\n93: ---\n94: \n95: <!-- ANCHOR:security -->\n96: ## Security\n97: \n98: - [ ] CHK-040 [P1] No new input surface or injection sink introduced by any fix\n99:   - **Evidence (target)**: c006 fix neutralizes the outer-shell expansion of user input; no other task adds an input surface\n100: - [ ] CHK-041 [P2] c006 self→self trust boundary documented in the fix note\n101:   - **Evidence (target)**: the §0 note records the operator-types-own-query boundary that justified P1-not-P0\n102: <!-- /ANCHOR:security -->\n103: ---\n104: \n105: <!-- ANCHOR:docs -->\n106: ## Documentation\n107: \n108: - [ ] CHK-050 [P1] Each reconciled phase doc passes `validate.sh --strict` (T033)\n109:   - **Evidence (target)**: exit 0 per touched 017-021 spec folder\n110: - [ ] CHK-051 [P1] No reconciliation overwrote a real `implementation-summary.md` (ADR-004)\n111:   - **Evidence (target)**: scaffold docs reconciled TO the impl-summary; impl-summary content untouched except 019/021 explicit wording fixes\n112: - [ ] CHK-052 [P2] This packet's own docs validate.sh --strict clean\n113:   - **Evidence (target)**: `validate.sh <this-packet> --strict` exit 0\n114: <!-- /ANCHOR:docs -->\n115: ---\n116: \n117: <!-- ANCHOR:file-org -->\n118: ## File Organization\n119: \n120: - [ ] CHK-060 [P1] This packet writes only its own folder; no reviewed code or 017-021 phase doc touched at authoring time\n121:   - **Evidence (target)**: `git status` shows changes confined to `006-deep-review-017-021-remediation/`\n122: - [ ] CHK-061 [P1] Temp/scratch files in scratch/ only; cleaned before completion\n123:   - **Evidence (target)**: no temp files outside `scratch/`\n124: <!-- /ANCHOR:file-org -->\n125: ---\n126: \n127: <!-- ANCHOR:arch-verify -->\n128: ## L3+: ARCHITECTURE VERIFICATION\n129: \n130: - [ ] CHK-100 [P0] Architecture decisions documented in decision-record.md\n131:   - **Evidence (target)**: ADR-001 (severity-lock), ADR-002 (honor verdicts), ADR-003 (workstream split), ADR-004 (reconcile-to-impl-summary)\n132: - [ ] CHK-101 [P1] All ADRs have status (Accepted)\n133:   - **Evidence (target)**: each ADR metadata status: Accepted\n134: <!-- /ANCHOR:arch-verify -->\n135: ---\n136: \n137: <!-- ANCHOR:perf-verify -->\n138: ## L3+: PERFORMANCE VERIFICATION\n139: \n140: - [ ] CHK-110 [P2] No carried fix degrades scan/search responsiveness (the reviewed deliverable's purpose)\n141:   - **Evidence (target)**: 021 fixes preserve cooperative-yield; the live max-event-loop-lag readout stays within the established bound (≤634ms baseline)\n142: - [ ] CHK-111 [P2] The c006 fix adds no measurable command-resolution latency\n143:   - **Evidence (target)**: `set -f`/restructure is O(1); arg-echo timing unchanged\n144: <!-- /ANCHOR:perf-verify -->\n145: ---\n146: \n147: <!-- ANCHOR:deploy-ready -->\n148: ## L3+: DEPLOYMENT READINESS\n149: \n150: - [ ] CHK-120 [P1] Rollback path documented per change class (code commit / doc git-revert / ephemeral marker)\n151:   - **Evidence (target)**: plan.md L2 Enhanced Rollback + ADR-001 rollback notes\n152: - [ ] CHK-121 [P2] Daemon recycle plan noted if a shipped lib/ change must go live\n153:   - **Evidence (target)**: dist rebuild + recycle is the implementation step's concern, recorded in its handover\n154: <!-- /ANCHOR:deploy-ready -->\n155: ---\n156: \n157: <!-- ANCHOR:compliance-verify -->\n158: ## L3+: COMPLIANCE VERIFICATION\n159: \n160: - [ ] CHK-130 [P1] No reviewed code or 017-021 phase doc touched at authoring time (scope-lock)\n161:   - **Evidence (target)**: `git status` confined to `006-…/`\n162: - [ ] CHK-131 [P1] Comment hygiene respected in any later code fix (no spec/packet ids in code comments)\n163:   - **Evidence (target)**: pre-commit gate passes; durable WHY only\n164: <!-- /ANCHOR:compliance-verify -->\n165: ---\n166: \n167: <!-- ANCHOR:docs-verify -->\n168: ## L3+: DOCUMENTATION VERIFICATION\n169: \n170: - [ ] CHK-140 [P1] This packet's six docs pass validate.sh --strict (exit 0)\n171:   - **Evidence (target)**: validation run recorded in implementation-summary verification table\n172: - [ ] CHK-141 [P1] Every task carries a synthesis trace + confidence tag\n173:   - **Evidence (target)**: tasks.md `<trace:…>` + `{confirmed-by-code|needs-in-task-verification}` on each task\n174: <!-- /ANCHOR:docs-verify -->\n175: ---\n176: \n177: <!-- ANCHOR:sign-off -->\n178: ## L3+: SIGN-OFF\n179: \n180: - [ ] CHK-150 [P1] Authoring step complete: 6 docs + 2 metadata files present, validate.sh --strict exit 0\n181:   - **Evidence (target)**: this checklist + the validation run\n182: - [ ] CHK-151 [P1] Handoff to implementation step is unambiguous (T001 severity-lock is the first action)\n183:   - **Evidence (target)**: spec next_safe_action = \"verify c006 renderer then begin per-file remediation\"\n184: <!-- /ANCHOR:sign-off -->\n185: ---\n186: \n187: <!-- ANCHOR:summary -->\n188: ## Verification Summary\n189: \n190: | Category | Total | Verified |\n191: |----------|-------|----------|\n192: | P0 Items | 5 | 0/5 (pending — authoring step) |\n193: | P1 Items | 13 | 0/13 (pending) |\n194: | P2 Items | 7 | 0/7 (pending) |\n195: \n196: **Authoring date**: 2026-06-17\n197: **Authored By**: deep-review-remediation-author\n198: **Status**: not-started — findings carried as tasks; no fixes applied\n199: **ADRs**: 4 documented, 4 accepted\n200: <!-- /ANCHOR:summary -->\n\n(End of file - total 200 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: \"Verification Checklist: Deep-Review 017-021 Remediation [027/002/005/006]\"\ndescription: \"Quality gates for the 017-021 remediation. Items are pending at authoring time; each names the evidence the later implementation step must capture. The P1 and the per-finding coverage are the load-bearing gates.\"\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"017-021 remediation checklist\"\n  - \"deep review remediation checklist\"\nimportance_tier: \"important\"\ncontextType: \"general\"\n_memory:\n  continuity:\n    packet_pointer: \"system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/005-verification-and-remediation/006-deep-review-017-021-remediation\"\n    last_updated_at: \"2026-06-17T00:00:00Z\"\n    last_updated_by: \"deep-review-remediation-author\"\n    recent_action: \"Authored verification gates incl. fix-completeness for 017-021 remediation\"\n    next_safe_action: \"verify c006 renderer then begin per-file remediation\"\n    blockers: []\n    completion_pct: 0\n---\n# Verification Checklist: Deep-Review 017-021 Remediation\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/005-verification-and-remediation/006-deep-review-017-021-remediation/checklist.md","text":"---\ntitle: \"Verification Checklist: Deep-Review 017-021 Remediation [027/002/005/006]\"\ndescription: \"Quality gates for the 017-021 remediation. Items are pending at authoring time; each names the evidence the later implementation step must capture. The P1 and the per-finding coverage are the load-bearing gates.\"\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"017-021 remediation checklist\"\n  - \"deep review remediation checklist\"\nimportance_tier: \"important\"\ncontextType: \"general\"\n_memory:\n  continuity:\n    packet_pointer: \"system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/005-verification-and-remediation/006-deep-review-017-021-remediation\"\n    last_updated_at: \"2026-06-17T00:00:00Z\"\n    last_updated_by: \"deep-review-remediation-author\"\n    recent_action: \"Authored verification gates incl. fix-completeness for 017-021 remediation\"\n    next_safe_action: \"verify c006 renderer then begin per-file remediation\"\n    blockers: []\n    completion_pct: 0\n---\n# Verification Checklist: Deep-Review 017-021 Remediation\n\n<!-- SPECKIT_LEVEL: 3 -->\n<!-- SPECKIT_TEMPLATE_SOURCE: checklist + level3-arch | v2.2 -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:protocol -->\n## Verification Protocol\n\n| Priority | Handling | Completion Impact |\n|----------|----------|-------------------|\n| **[P0]** | HARD BLOCKER | Cannot claim done until complete |\n| **[P1]** | Required | Must complete OR get user approval |\n| **[P2]** | Optional | Can defer with documented reason |\n\nItems below are PENDING — this is the authoring step; no fixes applied. Each item names the evidence the later implementation step must capture before marking `[x]`.\n<!-- /ANCHOR:protocol -->\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:pre-impl -->\n## Pre-Implementation\n\n- [ ] CHK-001 [P0] All confirmed findings extracted into tasks.md\n  - **Evidence (target)**: every CONFIRMED row across the five syntheses maps to exactly one task; no orphan, no fabrication\n- [ ] CHK-002 [P0] Rejected/refuted/already-resolved findings excluded\n  - **Evidence (target)**: §3 Out of Scope + tasks.md T034 enumerate the excluded items (018 mimo-1; 019/020 D6/D7/D8; 021 B8/A3)\n- [ ] CHK-003 [P1] Each task names a target file + concrete change + synthesis trace + confidence tag\n  - **Evidence (target)**: tasks.md notation block + per-task `<trace:…>` and `{confirmed-by-code|needs-in-task-verification}`\n<!-- /ANCHOR:pre-impl -->\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:code-quality -->\n## Code Quality\n\n- [ ] CHK-010 [P0] Each code fix is scoped to its synthesis-described change (no scope creep)\n  - **Evidence (target)**: diff per fix matches the cited remediation; reviewed deliverables stay behaviorally intact (NFR-C01)\n- [ ] CHK-011 [P1] c006 §0 hardening (if raw) handles glob/cmd-sub/metachar, not just word-splitting\n  - **Evidence (target)**: `set -f`/restructure applied; the shipped `\"$*\"` + `\"`-escape is superseded, not duplicated\n- [ ] CHK-012 [P1] `cancelledJobIds` cleared on EVERY terminal `setJobState` incl. `'failed'` (T012)\n  - **Evidence (target)**: job-store.ts delete on terminal transition; the `:69-75` \"cannot grow without bound\" comment is now literally true\n- [ ] CHK-013 [P1] Cited line numbers re-confirmed against live files before edit (esp. 021 :785-790/:802)\n  - **Evidence (target)**: each code task re-reads its cite (finding-is-a-hypothesis discipline)\n<!-- /ANCHOR:code-quality -->\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:testing -->\n## Testing\n\n- [ ] CHK-020 [P0] Baseline captured before changes; whole gate re-run after; delta reported\n  - **Evidence (target)**: `baseline N failing {…} → now M: {…}` per touched suite (T032)\n- [ ] CHK-021 [P1] New unit coverage for `processBatches` shouldAbort + `isCancelRequestedFast` Set lifecycle (T014-T015)\n  - **Evidence (target)**: batch-processor.vitest.ts + job-store.vitest.ts assert the new behavior\n- [ ] CHK-022 [P1] c006 metacharacter verification cases pass (if raw renderer)\n  - **Evidence (target)**: queries with `*`, `$(…)`, backticks, `;`, `\\|`, `&`, `>` resolve to the verbatim typed string; arg-echo matches\n- [ ] CHK-023 [P2] 019/020 test fixtures use the real `labels[]` shape; tests still pass (T022)\n  - **Evidence (target)**: launcher-maintenance-guard + daemon-reelection-adoption-live fixtures updated; suites green\n<!-- /ANCHOR:testing -->\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:fix-completeness -->\n## Fix Completeness\n\n- [ ] CHK-030 [P1] The single confirmed P1 (c006) is closed at its verified severity\n  - **Evidence (target)**: T001 establishes raw-vs-quoted; T002 quote-hardens (raw) or records a downgraded P2 doc-note (quoted), with renderer evidence cited\n- [ ] CHK-031 [P1] 017 systemic doc drift reconciled across all 7 children (T003)\n  - **Evidence (target)**: each child's spec/plan/tasks reflect shipped scope (or marked superseded); graph-metadata Status/Key Files match impl-summary\n- [ ] CHK-032 [P1] 019 doc cluster reconciled (paths, schema, TTL, limitation, module, fixtures) (T017-T022)\n  - **Evidence (target)**: `.opencode/bin/...` paths; `labels[]` schema; 180s TTL; per-tick embedding-queue protection; extracted module tracked\n- [ ] CHK-033 [P2] 018/021 cancellation + instrumentation P2s closed or accepted-with-reason\n  - **Evidence (target)**: T013/T027/T029/T030 done or each deferral documented against its synthesis\n- [ ] CHK-034 [P2] 017 c004 maintainability cluster + minor nits resolved or accepted-with-reason (T004-T011, T024-T026)\n  - **Evidence (target)**: each item fixed or carries a documented acceptance rationale\n<!-- /ANCHOR:fix-completeness -->\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:security -->\n## Security\n\n- [ ] CHK-040 [P1] No new input surface or injection sink introduced by any fix\n  - **Evidence (target)**: c006 fix neutralizes the outer-shell expansion of user input; no other task adds an input surface\n- [ ] CHK-041 [P2] c006 self→self trust boundary documented in the fix note\n  - **Evidence (target)**: the §0 note records the operator-types-own-query boundary that justified P1-not-P0\n<!-- /ANCHOR:security -->\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:docs -->\n## Documentation\n\n- [ ] CHK-050 [P1] Each reconciled phase doc passes `validate.sh --strict` (T033)\n  - **Evidence (target)**: exit 0 per touched 017-021 spec folder\n- [ ] CHK-051 [P1] No reconciliation overwrote a real `implementation-summary.md` (ADR-004)\n  - **Evidence (target)**: scaffold docs reconciled TO the impl-summary; impl-summary content untouched except 019/021 explicit wording fixes\n- [ ] CHK-052 [P2] This packet's own docs validate.sh --strict clean\n  - **Evidence (target)**: `validate.sh <this-packet> --strict` exit 0\n<!-- /ANCHOR:docs -->\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:file-org -->\n## File Organization\n\n- [ ] CHK-060 [P1] This packet writes only its own folder; no reviewed code or 017-021 phase doc touched at authoring time\n  - **Evidence (target)**: `git status` shows changes confined to `006-deep-review-017-021-remediation/`\n- [ ] CHK-061 [P1] Temp/scratch files in scratch/ only; cleaned before completion\n  - **Evidence (target)**: no temp files outside `scratch/`\n<!-- /ANCHOR:file-org -->\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:arch-verify -->\n## L3+: ARCHITECTURE VERIFICATION\n\n- [ ] CHK-100 [P0] Architecture decisions documented in decision-record.md\n  - **Evidence (target)**: ADR-001 (severity-lock), ADR-002 (honor verdicts), ADR-003 (workstream split), ADR-004 (reconcile-to-impl-summary)\n- [ ] CHK-101 [P1] All ADRs have status (Accepted)\n  - **Evidence (target)**: each ADR metadata status: Accepted\n<!-- /ANCHOR:arch-verify -->\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:perf-verify -->\n## L3+: PERFORMANCE VERIFICATION\n\n- [ ] CHK-110 [P2] No carried fix degrades scan/search responsiveness (the reviewed deliverable's purpose)\n  - **Evidence (target)**: 021 fixes preserve cooperative-yield; the live max-event-loop-lag readout stays within the established bound (≤634ms baseline)\n- [ ] CHK-111 [P2] The c006 fix adds no measurable command-resolution latency\n  - **Evidence (target)**: `set -f`/restructure is O(1); arg-echo timing unchanged\n<!-- /ANCHOR:perf-verify -->\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:deploy-ready -->\n## L3+: DEPLOYMENT READINESS\n\n- [ ] CHK-120 [P1] Rollback path documented per change class (code commit / doc git-revert / ephemeral marker)\n  - **Evidence (target)**: plan.md L2 Enhanced Rollback + ADR-001 rollback notes\n- [ ] CHK-121 [P2] Daemon recycle plan noted if a shipped lib/ change must go live\n  - **Evidence (target)**: dist rebuild + recycle is the implementation step's concern, recorded in its handover\n<!-- /ANCHOR:deploy-ready -->\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:compliance-verify -->\n## L3+: COMPLIANCE VERIFICATION\n\n- [ ] CHK-130 [P1] No reviewed code or 017-021 phase doc touched at authoring time (scope-lock)\n  - **Evidence (target)**: `git status` confined to `006-…/`\n- [ ] CHK-131 [P1] Comment hygiene respected in any later code fix (no spec/packet ids in code comments)\n  - **Evidence (target)**: pre-commit gate passes; durable WHY only\n<!-- /ANCHOR:compliance-verify -->\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:docs-verify -->\n## L3+: DOCUMENTATION VERIFICATION\n\n- [ ] CHK-140 [P1] This packet's six docs pass validate.sh --strict (exit 0)\n  - **Evidence (target)**: validation run recorded in implementation-summary verification table\n- [ ] CHK-141 [P1] Every task carries a synthesis trace + confidence tag\n  - **Evidence (target)**: tasks.md `<trace:…>` + `{confirmed-by-code|needs-in-task-verification}` on each task\n<!-- /ANCHOR:docs-verify -->\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:sign-off -->\n## L3+: SIGN-OFF\n\n- [ ] CHK-150 [P1] Authoring step complete: 6 docs + 2 metadata files present, validate.sh --strict exit 0\n  - **Evidence (target)**: this checklist + the validation run\n- [ ] CHK-151 [P1] Handoff to implementation step is unambiguous (T001 severity-lock is the first action)\n  - **Evidence (target)**: spec next_safe_action = \"verify c006 renderer then begin per-file remediation\"\n<!-- /ANCHOR:sign-off -->\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:summary -->\n## Verification Summary\n\n| Category | Total | Verified |\n|----------|-------|----------|\n| P0 Items | 5 | 0/5 (pending — authoring step) |\n| P1 Items | 13 | 0/13 (pending) |\n| P2 Items | 7 | 0/7 (pending) |\n\n**Authoring date**: 2026-06-17\n**Authored By**: deep-review-remediation-author\n**Status**: not-started — findings carried as tasks; no fixes applied\n**ADRs**: 4 documented, 4 accepted\n<!-- /ANCHOR:summary -->","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":200,"totalLines":200,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/005-verification-and-remediation/006-deep-review-017-021-remediation/checklist.md","time":{"start":1781762922381,"end":1781762922